      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "Southern and eastern borders of Aran, Shady slopes and high altitudes: The wind slabs are easy to recognise and prone to triggering. They are to be found in particular adjacent to ridgelines and in pass areas. The dry avalanches are rather small. Individual medium-sized avalanches are further not ruled out. <br/> <br/> Steep sunny slopes as well as low and intermediate altitudes: As a consequence of warming during the day and solar radiation moist snow slides and avalanches are to be expected as the day progresses. In addition a latent danger of gliding avalanches exists. <br/> <br/> Backcountry touring calls for meticulous route selection.",
        "highlights": "Moist snow slides and avalanches as the day progresses. Wind slabs at elevated altitudes."
